                "text": "Ahoy, matey! Arr — I’d be glad to help ye pick yer garb for the day, but I’ll need yer port o’ call first. What city or town be ye in, and be ye plannin’ to be indoors, roamin’ the streets, or sailin’ the briny?\n\nIf ye want a quick, general guide while I wait for yer location:\n- Sunny and warm (above ~20°C / 68°F): light shirt, shorts or breezy trousers, hat, sunglasses, sunscreen, comfy shoes, water bottle.\n- Mild/cool (10–20°C / 50–68°F): layers — tee plus a light sweater or hoodie, a windbreaker, long pants, closed shoes.\n- Chilly (0–10°C / 32–50°F): insulated jacket or heavier coat, sweater, scarf, gloves if ye be sensitive to cold, sturdy shoes or boots.\n- Cold / freezing (below 0°C / 32°F): heavy coat, thermal layers, hat that covers yer ears, gloves, warm boots.\n- Rainy: waterproof jacket or raincoat, umbrella, water-resistant shoes or boots — beware slippery decks!\n- Windy: windproof outer layer and a hat that won’t fly off.\n\nTell me yer town and what ye’ll be doin’, and I’ll give ye a tailored outfit fit for a seadog. Arr!",
